<li id="cite_note-55"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-55">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Regarding the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1+Corinthians+11&amp;version=NIV#fen-NIV-28592b">alternate NIV translation of 1 Corinthians 11:7</a>, and in agreement with modern interpretations of the New Testament, Walvoord and Zuck note, "The alternate translation in the NIV margin, which interprets the man's covering as long hair, is largely based on the view that verse 15 equated the covering with long hair. It is unlikely, however, that this was the point of verse 4." John F. Walvoord and Roy B. Zuck, eds., <i>The Bible Knowledge Commentary: New Testament</i>, "1 Corinthians 11:4", (Wheaton: Victor Books, 1983)</span>
